1. Definitions

1.1 "Engine Code"
Any portion of the software comprising development tools, editors, or any
code not intended to be included in a Compiled Artifact.

1.2 "Runtime Code"
Any portion of the software intended to be linked, embedded, or otherwise
included in a Compiled Artifact and required for its execution.

1.3 "Compiled Artifact"
Any software, application, or creative work that incorporates or links
against Runtime Code solely for the purpose of execution or use.

Compiled Artifact does not include tools, engines, or frameworks intended
to produce further Compiled Artifacts.

1.4 "Derivative Work"
Any work that:
(a) incorporates any portion of the Engine Code; or
(b) incorporates Runtime Code for the purpose of developing, generating,
    or enabling the creation of Compiled Artifacts.

Derivative Work does not include Compiled Artifacts.

1.5 "Corresponding Source"
The complete source code required to generate, install, and run the
Engine Code or Runtime Code, including any modifications, build scripts,
and interface definition files, as defined by the GNU General Public
License, version 3.

1.6 "Plugin"
Any software component designed to extend, modify, or interface with the
Runtime Code.

The classification of a Plugin as a Derivative Work is determined under
applicable law and is not altered by this License.

